[h1]Oxygen Not Included Together 1.0.2[/h1]

Current Stage: v1.0.2

Run one shared Oxygen Not Included colony with friends. Every player sees the same colony and can build, dig, manage priorities and schedules, control research, assign skills, operate rockets, and use the supported DLC systems.

[h2]Multiplayer[/h2]

[list]
[*]Steam friends lobbies with invite and lobby-code joining
[*]Steam relay/NAT traversal with no port forwarding or LAN tunnel
[*]Optional direct LAN connections
[*]Shared colony controls, player cursors, chat, pings, and drawings
[*]Host-authoritative actions with automatic state repair
[*]Full snapshot join and reconnect recovery
[*]Large-save transfer over TCP with automatic UDP fallback
[/list]

[h2]Supported content[/h2]

The release supports the base game, Spaced Out!, Frosty Planet Pack, Bionic Booster Pack, Prehistoric Planet Pack, Neutronium Cosmetics Pack, and Aquatic Planet Pack.

Every player must use an ONI Together DLL with the same SHA-256 and enable the same DLC set. A rejected client sees the specific DLL or DLC mismatch before world transfer. Other enabled Mods, load order, and configuration are not admission checks.

Steam multiplayer requires a separate Steam account for each running game instance. The host shares the lobby code or sends a Steam invite; SteamNetworkingSockets handles the Internet route.

[h2]Controls[/h2]

[list]
[*]Ctrl + right click: ping
[*]Ctrl + right drag: draw
[*]Ctrl + left click a drawing: delete it
[*]Shift + R: reset the chat window
[/list]

